        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 3:05PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 305 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Badin Lake, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts in excess of 30 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Asheboro, Albemarle, Troy, Badin Lake, Biscoe, Plyler, Badin, Star,
Candor, and Richfield.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
